OL,3,CTeen admits part in rocking police van
OL,4,Cduring Rotherham riot
OL,6,FAn 18-year-old man has admitted being
OL,7,Fpart of a crowd who violently rocked a
OL,8,Fpolice van during rioting in Rotherham.
OL,10,FFootage of the CCTV van being rocked
OL,11,Ffrom side to side, with its rooftop
OL,12,Fmast swinging, was widely shared on
OL,13,Fsocial media during the trouble at a
OL,14,FHoliday Inn Express hotel housing more
OL,15,Fthan 200 asylum seekers.
OL,17,FA neighbour of Kenzie Roughley, of
OL,18,FBarnsley Road, Pontefract, West
OL,19,FYorkshire, contacted police with video
OL,20,Ffootage of him punching and kicking
OL,21,Fthe vehicle.
